  "commentary": "With SPX at 6571.95 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-13.6B) and the GEX flip at 6602, dealers are currently in a stabilizing PIN regime where they'll provide liquidity by buying any dips toward 6550 and selling rallies toward the massive +17.8B gamma wall at 6600. The recent GEX surge combined with the -62% decline in 1-min change suggests dealers just absorbed significant hedging flow, likely from put buying or call selling, which should dampen volatility going forward. Key levels to watch are the 6550 amplifying support where dealer buying accelerates, and the 6600 brick wall where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect prices to get pinned between 6550-6600 with dealers smoothing out moves.",
